CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1954, pg. 12 reads: " Hill City Contestants For Queen - Among the organizations sponsoring some of these lovely young teenagers, who are striving to wear the Hill City Queen's crown at the may Coronation Ball, are Alpha Alpha Omega Chapter of AKA, Omicron Psi Chapter of Omega Fraternity, Hill City Women's Auxiliary, and Schenley Heights Neighborhood Club.  In this group are, left to right...Marilyn Bryant, Betty Brandon...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Marilyn Bryant wearing light colored sweater set, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of Betty Brandon wearing light colored neck scarf and two toned pullover with zigzag line across top and down sleeves, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest
